break out
Homonym Number:
Word Class: verb
Sense Number: 2
Definition:[shearing] to open out the fleece of a sheep as it is shorn up the neck.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
